metadata.name: Vorticity #24
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).

metadata.name: SC.002 : Studies Series #88
metadata.description:
This hybrid project combines elements of 2 previous drops: Glomularus + Inertial Packing. The project is intended as a giveaway to show appreciation to the community of collectors who previously have minted my work.

SC.002 includes multiple constraint systems, based on Verlet and Euler Integration approaches, with attached geometric primitives and softbody Prototubes. Numerous user controls are included:

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
-, +: reduce | increase Node Count
{, }: reduce | increase Packing Dimension
c, v: reduce | increase Node Adhesion
h, j: reduce | increase Node Jitter
b, n: disable| enable Node-Node Collision
z, x: reduce | increase Stick Constraint
a, s: hide | show Nodes
q, w: hide | show Wireframe
d, f: reduce | increase Prototube Thickness
p: screen capture

Tip:
1. There are 8 unique geometries, should you be inclined to collect a full set.
2. Bringing values outside of "rational" range is encouraged.

Note:
Please post your favorite SC.002 screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Asterium #137
metadata.description:
Asterium is a token that will grow with you, for an entire year. Changing and morphing over time to eventually reach its equilibrium.

It is a token where I try to symbolize the journey of life.
Where looking back is the best way to look forward.
Where looking into the future is not a possibility.
Where each day is as uncertain as the next.

A token that will surprise you and have its ups and downs as it grows over time.



Pricing:
Dutch auction 64-16-8, where anybody that picks one up at 64 tez gets a print of how their galaxy looks on any day from the present to day 0. Meaning you can claim the print at any point in the future.

The print will be printed on high quality hahnemühle torchon paper at 30x40 cm (11.81 x 15.75 in). Printed at a local print shop here in Utrecht. This paper has a rough texture to it that matches the textures of space perfectly.



Usage:
- Hover over your Asterium to view the name, date, days passed, status and render stats.
- Double press to export the current frame as a .png image.
- Use the slider at the bottom to scroll back in time to the days before today, you can go as far back as day 0 and as far forwards as today.
- The token refreshes every hour, so framing it in a digital picture frame is totally possible!

metadata.name: fx(mash) #349
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

metadata.name: A theory of General Instability #289
metadata.description:
« A theory of General Instability » is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, ZeroSpace NYC, 2023.

-----


🜂 ⇶ ⁂ Ω 🜁 ↺


Particles, forces, horizon.


∰ 🜴 🜔 ≋ ∂t ↺


----- 
* What/How *

2.5 millions particles are exposed to instabilities of a digital scalar force field. This quasi-simulation explores the shapes that result from a universe originated from changing sequences of events, with original irregularities of the order of less than 1 %.

Read more
https://danslesnuages.xyz/A-theory-of-General-Instability
https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/a-theory-of-general-instability

-----
* Mint preview / Capture *

Minter will get a 4K PNG (2160x2160px bitmap) and a randomly deterministic infinite generative animation.

----- 
* Technics *

This experience is designed to run on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on square or rectangle screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- Code written in JavaScript /  WebGL / ThreeJS / CuloriJS / GLSL shaders
- Unique random deterministic generative animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation
- Animation sequences duration between 12 and 36 seconds

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view (1080x1080 px) — limited to 3 captures by session

-----
@HAL09999 – April 12th, 2023
https://danslesnuages.xyz/about
https://twitter.com/HAL09999
https://danslesnuages.xyz/A-theory-of-General-Instability
L-DBMCCCKJIW

metadata.name: Punktwelt #464
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #185
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance
